{"RubricCriterion":[{"num":1,"description":"Active Directory design: domain structure, OU hierarchy, and group strategy with justification. (5 marks)","previous_version":null,"name":"A1 AD Design","criterion_scales":[68858756,68858757,68858758,68858759,68858760],"id":15572109,"value":16.67,"position":1,"rubric":1905795},{"position":2,"rubric":1905795,"value":23.33,"criterion_scales":[68858761,68858762,68858763,68858764,68858765],"id":15572110,"previous_version":null,"name":"A2 AD Config","num":2,"description":"Active Directory configuration evidence: annotated screenshots of DC installation, OUs, security groups, and GPO settings. (7 marks)"},{"previous_version":null,"name":"B1 Security","num":3,"description":"Network security policy document covering access control, audit and monitoring, and backup and recovery. (6 marks)","rubric":1905795,"position":3,"value":20,"criterion_scales":[68858766,68858767,68858768,68858769,68858770],"id":15572111},{"num":4,"description":"Security policy implementation evidence: NTFS/share permissions and audit policy with Event Viewer evidence. (5 marks)","previous_version":null,"name":"B2 Security","criterion_scales":[68858771,68858772,68858773,68858774,68858775],"value":16.67,"id":15572112,"position":4,"rubric":1905795},{"criterion_scales":[68858776,68858777,68858778,68858779,68858780],"value":13.33,"id":15572113,"position":5,"rubric":1905795,"description":"PowerShell bulk user creation script reading from users.csv, creating users in OUs, assigning groups, setting passwords, and producing a console summary. (4 marks)","num":5,"name":"C1 User","previous_version":null},{"criterion_scales":[68858781,68858782,68858783,68858784,68858785],"value":10,"id":15572114,"position":6,"rubric":1905795,"description":"PowerShell server health report script collecting CPU, memory, disk, and service status, writing a dated report file, and printing a console confirmation. (3 marks)","num":6,"name":"C2 Health","previous_version":null}],"RubricCriterionScale":[{"scale_value":12624558,"value":0,"description":"Domain structure is fully justified with correct functional level. OU hierarchy is complete, logical, and maps precisely to all three departments with sub-OUs for Users, Computers, and Groups. Security groups are correctly scoped (global/domain local) and their purposes are clearly articulated with reference to business requirements.","id":68858756,"criterion":15572109},{"description":"Domain structure is appropriate with minor gaps in justification. OU hierarchy covers all departments but sub-OU detail or naming is inconsistent. Group strategy is mostly correct with minor scope or purpose errors.","value":0,"id":68858757,"criterion":15572109,"scale_value":12624559},{"criterion":15572109,"description":"Domain structure is present but justification is thin. OU hierarchy addresses departments but misses sub-OUs or has structural gaps. Group strategy is partially correct; some scope or purpose elements are missing.","value":0,"id":68858758,"scale_value":12624560},{"scale_value":12624561,"value":0,"id":68858759,"description":"Domain structure is incomplete or unjustified. OU hierarchy does not adequately reflect business requirements. Group strategy is largely missing or incorrect.","criterion":15572109},{"scale_value":12624562,"criterion":15572109,"value":0,"description":"No Active Directory design submitted.","id":68858760},{"scale_value":12624558,"criterion":15572110,"value":0,"description":"All screenshots are present and clearly annotated. DC installation and domain creation (correct functional level), full OU hierarchy, at least 3 security groups with correct scope and membership, and a GPO with both password and screen lock policies are all demonstrated without gaps.","id":68858761},{"scale_value":12624559,"criterion":15572110,"id":68858762,"value":0,"description":"Most screenshots are annotated and cover the main configuration steps. Minor items may be missing (e.g., one group membership or one GPO setting) but the overall implementation is demonstrated clearly."},{"description":"Screenshots are provided but some are missing annotations or cover only part of the required configuration. At least the DC, some OUs, and one GPO setting are shown.","value":0,"id":68858763,"criterion":15572110,"scale_value":12624560},{"scale_value":12624561,"criterion":15572110,"value":0,"id":68858764,"description":"Few screenshots are present; most are unannotated or fail to demonstrate the required configuration steps. Major evidence gaps exist."},{"value":0,"description":"No configuration evidence submitted.","id":68858765,"criterion":15572110,"scale_value":12624562},{"id":68858766,"value":0,"description":"Policy document is professionally written and complete. Access control section specifies NTFS and share permissions with least-privilege references for all three shares. Audit section maps to specific Windows Server audit categories with realistic log review and retention details. Backup and recovery section defines backup type, frequency, retention, RTO, RPO, and tools clearly.","criterion":15572111,"scale_value":12624558},{"criterion":15572111,"value":0,"description":"Policy document covers all three sections with mostly complete content. One or two minor elements are missing or insufficiently detailed (e.g., RTO/RPO values are stated but not justified, or one audit category is omitted).","id":68858767,"scale_value":12624559},{"id":68858768,"value":0,"description":"Policy document addresses all three required sections but some content is superficial. NTFS/share permissions or audit categories may be partially described. Backup targets are present but incomplete.","criterion":15572111,"scale_value":12624560},{"value":0,"id":68858769,"description":"Policy document is incomplete; one or more sections are missing or too vague to be useful. Key elements such as NTFS permissions, audit categories, or recovery objectives are absent.","criterion":15572111,"scale_value":12624561},{"description":"No security policy document submitted.","value":0,"id":68858770,"criterion":15572111,"scale_value":12624562},{"criterion":15572112,"value":0,"description":"NTFS and share permissions for a departmental share are correctly configured and annotated screenshots align with the access control policy. At least two audit categories are enabled via GPO; Event Viewer evidence shows a captured event with a clear explanation of what the event demonstrates.","id":68858771,"scale_value":12624558},{"scale_value":12624559,"description":"NTFS/share permission screenshots are present and mostly aligned to the policy. Audit GPO settings are shown; Event Viewer evidence is present but the explanation of the captured event is brief or lacks detail.","value":0,"id":68858772,"criterion":15572112},{"criterion":15572112,"description":"One of the two security controls (NTFS permissions or audit policy) is demonstrated adequately; the other is partially shown or poorly annotated. Explanation of Event Viewer output is minimal.","value":0,"id":68858773,"scale_value":12624560},{"scale_value":12624561,"criterion":15572112,"description":"Screenshots are present but unannotated or do not correspond to the stated policy. Audit evidence or NTFS configuration is not clearly demonstrated.","value":0,"id":68858774},{"criterion":15572112,"value":0,"id":68858775,"description":"No security implementation evidence submitted.","scale_value":12624562},{"scale_value":12624558,"id":68858776,"value":0,"description":"Script reads and correctly processes all CSV fields. All users are created in the correct departmental OUs. Group membership is assigned correctly for each department. Password is set with force-change-at-next-logon enabled. Console summary clearly reports created and skipped counts. CSV contains at least 9 users across all three departments.","criterion":15572113},{"criterion":15572113,"id":68858777,"value":0,"description":"Script reads the CSV and creates users with minor issues (e.g., one OU path slightly incorrect, or group assignment missing for one department). Password handling is correct. Console summary is present.","scale_value":12624559},{"scale_value":12624560,"criterion":15572113,"value":0,"id":68858778,"description":"Script runs but has notable errors: some users placed in wrong OUs, group membership partially assigned, or force-change flag missing. Console summary is present but incomplete."},{"value":0,"id":68858779,"description":"Script has significant errors or does not run correctly. CSV processing is flawed or users are not created in the correct OUs. Group membership and/or password handling are largely absent.","criterion":15572113,"scale_value":12624561},{"scale_value":12624562,"criterion":15572113,"id":68858780,"value":0,"description":"No script submitted or script does not execute."},{"scale_value":12624558,"value":0,"description":"Script collects all required metrics (CPU %, available memory in MB, disk used/free per volume in GB, status of at least 2 services). Report is written to a correctly named file (ServerHealthReport_yyyyMMdd.txt) with readable formatting. Console confirmation message includes the full file path.","id":68858781,"criterion":15572114},{"description":"Script collects most metrics with minor omissions (e.g., disk per volume not broken out, or only one service checked). Report file name is correct. Console confirmation is present.","value":0,"id":68858782,"criterion":15572114,"scale_value":12624559},{"criterion":15572114,"description":"Script collects some metrics but misses one or two required items. Report file is created but may have naming or formatting issues. Console confirmation may be absent or incomplete.","value":0,"id":68858783,"scale_value":12624560},{"criterion":15572114,"value":0,"description":"Script attempts to collect metrics but has significant errors or missing data. Report file may not be created or named correctly. Console confirmation is missing.","id":68858784,"scale_value":12624561},{"id":68858785,"value":0,"description":"No script submitted or script does not execute.","criterion":15572114,"scale_value":12624562}],"RubricScale":[{"rubric":1905795,"position":1,"value":100,"id":12624558,"name":"Excellent","num":1},{"name":"Good","num":2,"rubric":1905795,"position":2,"value":75,"id":12624559},{"name":"Satisfactory","num":3,"position":3,"rubric":1905795,"id":12624560,"value":50},{"num":4,"name":"Needs Work","value":25,"id":12624561,"position":4,"rubric":1905795},{"id":12624562,"value":0,"rubric":1905795,"position":5,"num":5,"name":"Not Attempted"}],"Rubric":[{"scale_values":[12624558,12624559,12624560,12624561,12624562],"name":"Assessment D Rubric","criterion_scales_all":[68858756,68858757,68858758,68858759,68858760,68858761,68858762,68858763,68858764,68858765,68858766,68858767,68858768,68858769,68858770,68858771,68858772,68858773,68858774,68858775,68858776,68858777,68858778,68858779,68858780,68858781,68858782,68858783,68858784,68858785],"papers_scored":1,"total_points":null,"id":1905795,"criterion":[15572109,15572110,15572111,15572112,15572113,15572114],"owner":1179196701,"description":null,"distribute_criterion_percentage":0,"rubric_group":null,"scoring_method":2,"cv_loaded":"1","is_starred":0,"deleted":0}]}